com.tsgrp.migration.event.pipeline

Class PipelineResultWriter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.pipeline.PipelineResultWriter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PipelineEndDisengageEventListener

    public class PipelineResultWriter
extends AbstractListener
implements PipelineEndDisengageEventListener
    PipelineResultWriter writes out the following information for each Node, plus any "extra" NodeAttributes specified in the attributesToLog property.
    • Source ID
    • Queue ID
    • Target ID(s)
    • Current date/time
    The PrintWriter is initialized, and the header row is written, the first time writeNode is called. It is released during disengage.

    MigrationNode Attributes Read

    • om_source_id
    • om_target_id
